// This Node.js application allows you to monitor the uptime of various websites. 
// You can easily add or remove sites by updating the sites.json file.

// Adding a New Site

// 1.Open the sites.json file in the root directory of the project.

// 2.Locate the array of site objects, each with a name, url, and history field.

// 3.To add a new site, insert a new object with the following structure:

// sites.json

// {
//   "name": "Site Name",
//   "url": "https://example.com",
//   "history": []
// }

// name: The name of the site.
// url: The URL of the site you want to monitor.
// history: An empty array that will store the status history of the site.
// Save the sites.json file.



// Removing a Site

// 1.Open the sites.json file in the root directory of the project.
// 2.Locate the array of site objects.
// 3.To remove a site, find the object corresponding to the site you want to remove and delete it.
// 4.Save the sites.json file.


//sites.json File

// [
//   {
//     "name": "Example Site 1",
//     "url": "https://example1.com",
//     "history": []
//   },
//   {
//     "name": "Example Site 2",
//     "url": "https://example2.com",
//     "history": []
//   }
//   // Add or remove sites as needed
// ]
// Important Notes
// Ensure that the JSON syntax is correct after making changes.
// Make sure to maintain the integrity of the history field as it stores the status records for each site.